                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18320105-196-off1095 t18320105-196-crimeloc1097"></join>. On the 29th of November, between five and six o'clock in the evening, I lost a bedstead; I had seen it safe half an hour before - they left one leg behind, and the broker had one made.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320105-196-person1744">
                  JOHN 
                  PARROTT
               <interp inst="t18320105-196-person1744" type="surname" value="PARROTT"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-196-person1744" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18320105-196-person1744" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a broker, and live in Queen-street, Seven-dials. On the evening of the 29th of November, the prisoner came to my shop with another young man, who carried a bedstead; the prisoner said he had a bedstead for sale, and asked if I would buy it - he asked 3s. 6d. for it; I offered him 3s. - he went away, came back again, and said if I would stand a quartern of gin I should have it for 3s. - I gave him the 3s.; we all three then went to a public-house, and had the gin - the prisoner afterwards came with an iron pot; I gave him into custody - he said his father bought the bedstead for him six months before; it wanted a leg - I did not know him before.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18320105-196-person1745">
